 Ugbagwu, 42, was out with his wife and returned home after
receiving calls on his mobile phone, the Lagos-based newspaper
reported. He was shot by gunmen in a red car near his house, the
newspaper reported.  
 Last year Bayo Ohu, an assistant politics editor at the
Guardian newspaper, was shot at his residence in Lagos.  
